				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Highsun Questions<a name="5234"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 7 03 12:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I am just about to hit 56 (finally) and was just on a rare raid with a second bard. He was 56th and has this song, though I didn't talk to him about it.  I also just read about this song in a thread here, so it peaked my curiosity.  For those of you that have this song and have used it, please fill me in...
<br />

<br />
Ok, I know that this song gates a mob back to it's spawn point, but...
<br />

<br />
1) Is it unresistable, or how often does it land? 
<br />

<br />
2) Does it erase aggro, or will the mob and his friends come running after us?  
<br />

<br />
3) Does it gain us aggro to use it?
<br />

<br />
4) Is there a level max on it, or could I use it to repostition mobs in ToV, or help on a fear break-in to weed out some of the mobs that have followed us from the zone-in area to the &quot;safe spot&quot;?
<br />

<br />
If the answers to these questions are as I hope, this could be a very useful situational song.  Especially as my alliance wiped on a fear breakin last night and it took nearly 3 hours to recover the corpses.  If I could have picked off a few of them by porting them half-way across the zone (whereever they spawned), that may very well have saved the day.  Of course if they don't lose aggro, that would have just caused a BIGGER train including Cazic Thule himself.... baaaad idea.
<br />

<br />
You see my confusion. I didn't see anything on the songs listing that answered this so I thought I'd ask.  Thanks,
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
