			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Song of Highsun<a name="5324"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 11 03 9:22 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>
<br />

<br />
This is a very very very good song.
<br />

<br />
Since we can't mass mezz like chanters, sometimes
<br />
it's our &quot;when h*ll breaks loose&quot; song.  It allowed us
<br />
to camp clerics in PoH when the break in went awry.
<br />

<br />
Of course, whenever using this song around people,
<br />
expect to confuse everyone of them.  The song doesn't
<br />
say &quot;Stuce gates an orc centurion&quot;, it says &quot;orc centurion
<br />
gates&quot;, so people think the mobs all suddenly started gating.
<br />

<br />
The song itself doesn't clear aggro, and I've found that even
<br />
completely across some zones, green mobs would eventually
<br />
find me.
<br />

<br />
The song can be partially resisted, so mobs immune to stun
<br />
can still be gated.
<br />

<br />
With the advent of PoP however, this song becomes extremely
<br />
powerful.  I don't want to go into all the details of what you
<br />
can do because of a probable imminent nerf, but I'll say this;
<br />

<br />
fading memories...
<br />

<br />
Astuce Subterfuge
<br />
Elysiam's Triad
<br />
Innoruuk Server</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
